programme.desc: Buzz finds a new friend at the playground, Jojo makes waka rererangi and Tama, Maia & Jojo have friends round for tea.

programme.title: Aussie Bush Tales
programme.desc: The Elder Moort was getting hungry for some Bungarra to eat, he sent the three Aboriginal boys to catch one. They were fooled by the old Bungarra and found a camel that was stuck in a rabbit warren.

programme.title: Bushwhacked
programme.desc: A, L. Kayne and Kamil set off to Uluru in search of Australia's greatest monitor, the perentie, but not without meeting some very special desert folk along the way!

programme.title: Fresh Fairytales
programme.desc: Princess Piuti is cursed by the evil Mele Fiseni to a lifetime of stinky breath, facial hair, and a deep sleep from her 16th birthday.

programme.title: The Magic Canoe
programme.desc: Nico makes others angry because he 'cries wolf' to get their attention. His comical adventure will make him realize that 'crying wolf' can have unpleasant consequences!

programme.title: Motown Magic
programme.desc: Angie wants to turn back time to when her parents were together, so Ben helps her enter Street Art World to seek guidance from a wise graffiti oracle.

programme.title: Spartakus And The Sun Beneath The Sea
programme.desc: Audio Described (AD). Without suspecting that they are being watched and followed by pirates, our heroes venture into a jungle which shelters strange remains.

programme.title: Waabiny Time
programme.desc: Maara, hands and djena, feet are very useful to us and together with the other parts of our body help us every day. Maara baam, hands clap and djena kakarook, feet dance. It's too deadly koolangka.

programme.title: Wolf Joe
programme.desc: While tobogganing, Joe, Nina and Buddy rescue Handyman Hank when his delivery snowmobile breaks down then use their skills to save the Winter Solstice party.

programme.title: The World According To Grandpa
programme.desc: Connie asks 'Why do the seasons change?' and Grandpa spins a tall tale about four rhubarb-loving monsters who live inside the planet and the little girl who teaches them a lesson.

programme.title: Volcanic Odysseys
programme.desc: Audio Described (AD). In this episode Volcanologist Tom Pfeiffer leads an expedition looking at the influences and affects of Mexico's great volcanos have had on it's people, culture and history.

programme.desc: The latest news from the oldest living culture, Join Natalie Ahmat and the team of NITV journalists for stories from an Indigenous perspective.
